    {
      "index": 1046,
      "page_content": "{'column_name': 'field', 'table_name': 'PolicyCondition', 'type': 'varchar', 'description': 'Identifier type used in the policy condition, indicating the specific aspect of the asset finding being evaluated.', 'properties': {'description': 'field refers to the type of identifier used in the condition of the policy.  The available value is versioned and hierarchical:\\n- `snyk/asset/finding/v1` : identity of the finding scoped to a Snyk assets (e.g. a repository).\\nFor a given issue, `snyk/asset/finding/v1` can be extracted from the `key_asset` field in the [issues API](https://apidocs.snyk.io/?version=2024-10-15#get-/orgs/-org_id-/issues). \\nIn addition, finding identities can be extracted from the fingerprints section of the SARIF, which is accessible via the Snyk CLI. More details can be found in the [CLI documentation](https://docs.snyk.io/snyk-cli/scan-and-maintain-projects-using-the-cli/snyk-cli-for-snyk-code/view-snyk-code-cli-results#export-test-results).\\n', 'business_significance': 'Essential for defining the scope of the policy condition, allowing for targeted enforcement based on specific identifiers like Snyk asset findings.'}}",
      "metadata": {
        "content_type": "column_definition",
        "column_name": "field",
        "table_name": "PolicyCondition",
